Issues.Body:
### Is your feature request related to a problem? Please describe

Based on [CA1066](https://docs.microsoft.com/lv-lv/dotnet/fundamentals/code-analysis/quality-rules/ca1066) it looks like there are some missing IEquatable<T> interface implementations for the following public types:

- BindingMemberInfo
- LinkArea
- TableLayoutPanelCellPosition
- Message
- Padding

There was a similar issue in https://github.com/dotnet/runtime/issues/63687.

### Describe the solution you'd like and alternatives you've considered

To address the warnings we can add the following items.

```csharp
public struct BindingMemberInfo : IEquatable<BindingMemberInfo>
{
    public bool Equals(BindingMemberInfo other) { }
}

public struct LinkArea : IEquatable<LinkArea>
{
    public bool Equals(LinkArea other) { }
}

public struct TableLayoutPanelCellPosition : IEquatable<TableLayoutPanelCellPosition>
{
    public bool Equals(TableLayoutPanelCellPosition other) { }
}

public struct Message : IEquatable<Message>
{
    public bool Equals(Message other) { }
}

public struct Padding : IEquatable<Padding>
{
    public bool Equals(Padding other) { }
}
```

### Will this feature affect UI controls?

It shouldn't require more changes than the ones in the associated PR.
